posts.name: Bryant's Breakfast
posts.note: Bryant's Breakfast is a bustling, counter-serve eatery dishing out classic Southern breakfast and lunch fare. Unless you get to Bryant's Breakfast when they open, plan on having to wait in line for an hour or more. I ordered two breakfast sandwiches, and my favorite was the Bologna with egg and cheese on a biscuit.

posts.name: Charlie Vergos' Rendezvous
posts.note: Charlie Vergos' Rendezvous is a BBQ spot with upstairs beer hall serving up racks of smoked ribs and sausages dusted with dry rub. Need to order the lamb riblets, which is their sleeper dish. I still think about the lamb riblets when I talk about BBQ to people or Memphis.

posts.name: Dyer's Burgers
posts.note: Dyer's Burgers is a popular diner known for using the same grease to deep-fry their burgers and fries for over a century.

posts.name: Lunchbox Eats
posts.note: Lunchbox Eats is a laid-back eatery serving sandwiches, comfort food, and desserts in a casual space with patio seating. Order the graduation meatloaf sandwich or turkey sandwich with home made slaw.

posts.name: Payne's Bar-B-Que
posts.note: Payne's Bar-B-Que is a simple cinder block building serving acclaimed chopped and pulled pork sandwiches along with smoked sausage too.
